git init

git init: Use git init to create a new git repository. before we can do anything,
          we must initialize a repo first !

kunalchavan@Kunals-MacBook-Pro GitCommandPractice % ls -a
.		..		.git		test.txt

kunalchavan@Kunals-MacBook-Pro GitCommandPractice % cd .git
kunalchavan@Kunals-MacBook-Pro .git % ls
config		description	HEAD		hooks		info		objects		refs
kunalchavan@Kunals-MacBook-Pro .git %

kunalchavan@Kunals-MacBook-Pro .git % cd ..
kunalchavan@Kunals-MacBook-Pro GitCommandPractice %
kunalchavan@Kunals-MacBook-Pro GitCommandPractice % rm -rf .git
kunalchavan@Kunals-MacBook-Pro GitCommandPractice % git status
fatal: not a git repository (or any of the parent directories): .git
kunalchavan@Kunals-MacBook-Pro GitCommandPractice % git init
Initialized empty Git repository in /Users/kunalchavan/GitCommandPractice/.git/